Enable Actions for CRM Analytics Lenses and Dashboards
Perform Actions on a Salesforce Record from CRM Analytics

You can invoke a Salesforce action on the record directly from CRM Analytics.
User permissions are required to edit a dataset, create actions, and customize application.

CRM Analytics supports object and global actions defined in Salesforce:
Create, update, and change owner actions for object records.
Log a Call actions.
Custom actions to invoke flows, Lightning components, and Visualforce Pages.

Actions assigned to a page layout for the User object aren't supported.

To configure actions from a dataset:

Edit the dataset.
Click Configure Actions button ().
Select the dataset field where you want the action menu to appear.
Choose which dataset fields to show users.

To let users open a Salesforce record or URL, select Open Salesforce record and enter a tooltip.

Choose one of the following actions:
Salesforce Record
Opens the Salesforce record.
Salesforce Record (Multiple Orgs)
Opens the Salesforce record from another org.
URL
Opens a URL that uses HTTP or HTTPS protocols.
Perform Salesforce actions

Configure actions from a table:

From the table view in a lens, select Configure Actions.
In the Record ID Field, select the dataset field that contains the record ID of the object that you want to perform the action on.

To let users update an opportunity record from CRM Analytics, add the Update Opportunity action to the Opportunity Name field in a CRM Analytics dataset.
title: Configuring Actions in CRM Analytics
